	<name>Gradia</name>
	<summary>Make your screenshots ready for all</summary>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">@APP_ID@.desktop</launchable>
	<description>
		<p>Gradia helps you quickly prepare your screenshots for sharing by fixing common issues like transparency and awkward sizing. With simple tools to add backgrounds, adjust aspect ratios, and annotate images, you can enhance your screenshots to look professional and consistent across social media, blogs, and other platforms on the internet.</p>
		<p>Key features:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Add optional image and gradient backgrounds to your images</li>
			<li>Adjust aspect ratios and padding to fit different platforms</li>
			<li>Ten annotation modes, including text, arrow, and censor</li>
			<li>Multiple ways to import and export screenshots</li>
		  <li>Quick upload button for image services like Imgur</li>
		</ul>
		<!-- Package maintainers, please replace with correct command -->
		<p>Want a keyboard shortcut on GNOME? Simply go to Settings → Keyboard → View and Customize Shortcuts → Custom Shortcuts.
    Then create a shortcut that runs
			<code>flatpak run be.alexandervanhee.gradia --screenshot=INTERACTIVE</code>.
		</p>
	</description>
	<developer id="io.github.alexandervanhee">
		<name>Alexander Vanhee</name>
	</developer>
